a > 1
x\leq y
\frac{a + \sin{x}}{a + \sin{y}} \leq \exp(y-x)
a = \displaystyle{\frac{e^\pi +1}{e^\pi -1}}
\sin{x}=1
\sin{y}=-1
y-x = \pi
a
ae^x+\sin xe^x\leq ae^y+\sin y e^y
f(x)=ae^x+\sin xe^x
f'(x)=ae^x+\cos x e^x+\sin x e^x
a=\sqrt{2}
f'\geq 0
a
\sqrt{2}
ae^x+\cos x e^x+\sin x e^x\geq 0\Rightarrow a\geq-\cos x-\sin x=-\sqrt{2}\cos\left(x-\frac{\pi}{4}\right)\Rightarrow
a\geq-\sqrt{2}\cos\left(\frac{5\pi}{4}-\frac{\pi}{4}\right)=\sqrt{2}
